+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified all visible review threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing:
+
+- Actionable: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, `T-214-05`
+- Duplicate: `T-214-02`
+- Obsolete: `T-214-03`
+
+`artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was treated as stale scratch context only and not used as the authority for thread state.
+
+## Code Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  - Applied `normalize_approval_state(...)` inside `build_policy_preview(...)` before building the preview payload.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  - Preserved `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the `preview_unavailable` fallback payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  - Added regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  - Corrected the fallback payload example to show the normalized human-review fields.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `python3 -m unittest tests/test_preview.py`
+- `python3 -m unittest tests/test_approval_router.py`
+
+Both test runs passed.
+
+## Outcome
+
+`build_policy_preview(request_id="req-214", approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, actor="review-bot")` now returns a fallback payload that keeps:
+
+- `"approval_state": "human_review_required"`
+- `"requires_human_review": true`
+
+No legacy branch or legacy preview hint was introduced.
