+## PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+
+Fixed. `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before delegating, and `build_preview_payload(...)` preserves `approval_state` plus `requires_human_review` on the `preview_unavailable` fallback payload.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate. This is the same reopened fallback preview regression as `T-214-01`, so no separate code change was applied.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete. The comment points at an outdated diff hunk and asks to revive legacy behavior on the current branch, which was intentionally not applied.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Fixed. Added a regression in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and asserting the normalized fallback payload stays on `human_review_required`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Fixed. Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example includes `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
